race.comment: CARDONETTE (7) draws awkwardly but will take beating building on her nose defeat at Eagle Farm on debut jumping a $2.50 favourite. She didn't get it easy and impressed. Thomson stays aboard and the filly is sure to keep improving for the premier Gollan yard. ON POINT PIXIE (9) did about what was expected at Eagle Farm first up over this distance and three back wasn't beaten far here in Stakes grade. Brings a trial win and can feature with average luck in the run. BRAVE MONARCH (5) debuted in the CARDONETTE race beaten 2.5L. He's just missed since in a trial here and can make the finish. KING COBAMA (1) missed a whisker at the Sunshine Coast on debut and will build on that. The 3kg claim is handy but the gate is awkward. TILIA (15) resumed at Eagle Farm for Gollan and disappointed (vet cleared). She'd raced well on debut and had trialled well. Graham replaces Thompson and an improved effort is likely at a price.
